Por ello, buscamos incorporar a personas que aspiren a construir una minería más sustentable e inclusiva.

Ingeniera(o) Senior Mantenimiento – Eléctrico e Instrumentación – Turno 4x3 – Compañía Minera Los Pelambres

Estamos en búsqueda de una(un) profesional con capacidad para asegurar la correcta ejecución del mantenimiento en acuerdo con los estándares de seguridad, alcances y programación, acorde a la estrategia de mantenimiento en el largo, mediano y corto plazo.

 Asesorar técnicamente a Superintendente de ejecución en problemas de alta complejidad y ser un referente técnico para los jefes de turno.  Ejecutar el trabajo en base a altos estándares de seguridad y la priorización de la tarea en cumplimiento de los procesos de Administración del Trabajo en SAP.  Ser un articulador y realizar todas las gestiones pertinentes para convocar a las áreas de planificación, operación, confiabilidad y áreas externas al mantenimiento como proyectos, con el fin de asegurar los compromisos en la ejecución del mantenimiento.  Asegurar disponibilidad de recursos en forma oportuna y de manera eficiente. 
¿Qué requisitos debes cumplir?
 Título profesional de Ingeniería Civil o Ejecución Eléctrica o Electrónica.  Poseer al menos 10 años de experiencia en funciones similares de mantenimiento eléctrico de correas transportadoras, regenerativas de alta tensión y chancadores primarios del tipo giratorios.  Conocimiento en chancadores primarios: Funcionamiento de chancadores, Sistema de Control DeltaV y Multilin  Conocimiento en sistemas de control S7 400, Simadyn, Sinamics.  Conocimiento en filosofías de control de correas regenerativas con frenos Jonhson.  Deseable manejo en metodologías de mejora continua.  Conocimientos Sistemas PLC, Alta potencia.  Conocimientos y manejo de sistema SAP PM.  Licencia de conducir clase B, para conducción de alta montaña.  Disponibilidad para trabajar presencialmente en sistema de turno 4x3 en faena ubicada en la Región de Coquimbo.

FullStack Labs is the fastest-growing software consultancy in the Americas. We help organizations like Uber, GoDaddy, MGM, Siemens, Stanford University, and the State of California, build distributed software development teams, and deliver transformational digital solutions. As an employee-first company, we focus on hiring the most talented software designers and developers in the western hemisphere, by creating a positive, respectful, and supportive work environment where they can achieve their greatest potential.

We’re most proud of:
Offering life-changing career opportunities to talented software professionals across the Americas.Building highly-skilled software development teams for hundreds of the world’s greatest companies.Having delivered hundreds of successful custom software solutions, which have positively impacted the lives and careers of millions of users.Our 4.7-star rating on GlassDoor.Our client Net Promoter Score of 64, twice the industry average.Sustained growth of 100% - 200% per year.

The Position:

We're looking to hire several senior Product Managers to manage 1 - 3 software development projects at a time. Primary responsibilities will include:
Client communication.Sprint planning.Helping estimate sprints, projects, delivery milestones, etc.Running daily standups.Coordinating work across a remote development team (designers, QA, developers, client).Ensuring projects are completed on time and on budget.Enforcing technical best practices.

Team Augmentation / Staffing: You will integrate yourself directly into our client's team and work alongside their existing designers and engineers on a daily basis.Design & Build: You will work on a FullStack Labs product team to build and deliver a product to our clients.

What We're Looking For:

Must-Have: 
Scrum certification.High level of ownership.Forensic attention to detail.The ability to work independently and figure things out.You're a professional that takes pride in your work.Good communication skills.Desire to continually improve and learn.Team player who is open to receiving, and acting on feedback.

General Requirements: 
Excellent time management skills. You're able to pivot quickly from one contextual focus to another easily.You have a well-defined knowledge of modern application development (Ruby, PHP, JS, SQL, React, Angular, etc.) You should be able to advise on architectural decisions related to a project and be able to determine "bad" from good during code reviews.You're comfortable communicating and working over video calls using Zoom, Google Meet, etc. A good portion of your week will be spent communicating with clients. You should have a calm, professional demeanor, be prepared for meetings, and always be on time.Ability to manage and guide junior developers. Your team will look up to you to define the morale and pace of the project, this should be a natural extension of your personality.A commitment to quality at all times. It’s critical that you understand the difference between a good app and a bad one. You must be able to determine what clients/users will want, then have the ability to direct your team to build it.Ability to lead and motivate your teamAbility to ensure our project management process is being followedExperience leading teams using agile / scrumExperience with Jira.
